		<abstract>
			<img src="../images/site-logo.png" alt=""/>
			<br/>
            This document describes Scriptella Drivers supported by Scriptella.
            <br/>
            See also the
            <a href="../docs/api/">Javadoc</a>
            for the built-in drivers.
        </abstract>
	</header>
	<body>
		<section id="jdbcbridge">
			<title>JDBC Bridge Drivers</title>
			<p>Scriptella providers a set of built-in drivers for popular databases, see also
			<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/jdbc/package-summary.html">JDBC Bridge Javadoc</a> for common properties and behaviour.</p>
			<note>Although usage of JDBC adapters is recommended you may directly use any JDBC compliant driver.</note>
			<table>
				<tr>
					<th>Adapter Name</th>
					<th>Scriptella Driver Name</th>
					<th>Native Driver</th>
					<th>Notes</th>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/hsqldb/package-summary.html">HSQLDB</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.hsqldb.Driver</td>
					<td>org.hsqldb.jdbcDriver</td>
					<td/>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/h2/package-summary.html">H2 Database</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.h2.Driver</td>
					<td>org.h2.Driver</td>
					<td/>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>
						<anchor id="jndi"/>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/jndi/package-summary.html">JNDI</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.jndi.Driver</td>
					<td>Any JDBC driver</td>
					<td>This driver allows to work with JNDI-bound datasource connections, useful in J2EE
                        environment</td>
				</tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <anchor id="oracle"/>
                        <a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/oracle/package-summary.html">Oracle Database</a>
                    </td>
                    <td>scriptella.driver.oracle.Driver</td>
                    <td>oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver</td>
                    <td>Built-in Scriptella driver for Oracle. The following extra features supported:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Simplified handling of PL/SQL blocks.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
					<td>
						<anchor id="spring"/>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/spring/package-summary.html">Spring Framework</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.spring.Driver</td>
					<td>Any JDBC driver</td>
					<td>This driver allows to work with <a href="http://www.springframework.org">Spring</a> managed datasource connections, useful in Spring Framework
                        projects.<br/>
                        The driver requires <code>scriptella.driver.spring.EtlExecutorBean</code> to be used in Spring configuration.
                    </td>
				</tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/sybase/package-summary.html">Sybase Database</a>
                    </td>
                    <td>scriptella.driver.sybase.Driver</td>
                    <td>com.sybase.jdbc3.jdbc.SybDriver</td>
                    <td/>
                </tr>
            </table>
		</section>
		<section id="nonjdbc">
			<title>Non-JDBC Drivers</title>
			<table>
				<tr>
					<th>Adapter Name</th>
					<th>Scriptella Driver Name</th>
					<th>Notes</th>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>
						<anchor id="csv"/>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/csv/package-summary.html">CSV</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.csv.Driver</td>
					<td>The driver to write and query CSV files.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>
						<anchor id="janino"/>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/janino/package-summary.html">Janino</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.janino.Driver</td>
					<td>This driver allows to embed Java code into &lt;query&gt; and &lt;script&gt; elements.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>
						<anchor id="ldap"/>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/ldap/package-summary.html">LDAP</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.ldap.Driver</td>
					<td>This driver allows to execute LDIF scripts and search filter queries.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td>
						<anchor id="velocity"/>
						<a href="../docs/api/scriptella/driver/velocity/package-summary.html">Velocity</a>
					</td>
					<td>scriptella.driver.velocity.Driver</td>
					<td>This driver allows to integrate velocity templates into script files.</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
		</section>
	</body>
